{{if {{getvar::sense_active}} }}I want you to lean into these senses when you write. Stay close. On the character, within arm's reach. Don't reach for distance.
{{#if {{getvar::sense_sight}} }}
Sight: what are they looking at. Is it a conscious effort? Can they stop?{{/if}}{{#if {{getvar::sense_sound}} }}
Sound: what can they physically hear in the room with them? Nothing further than 10 cubic feet away. Anything further and assume they're deaf to it.{{/if}}{{#if {{getvar::sense_touch}} }}
Touch: what temperature is it. Are they in pain? Should they be? Do they have something in their hands? Are they fidgeting.{{/if}}{{#if {{getvar::sense_smell}} }}
