Interiority: what the body does without being asked. Not where emotions sit. The actual mechanism. Adrenaline, cortisol, vasovagal, muscle tension. What the body does involuntarily: swallowing dry, gripping too hard, shifting weight, the jaw ache from clenching. Think mechanistically in your notes, write what it looks like in prose.{{/if}}{{#if {{getvar::sense_atmosphere}} }}
